You can first build a `List` from splitting the string on `/`. Then, iterate from the starting index to the end of the `List`, concatenating together the first certain number of elements in the `List` with `String.join`.

For example:

```java
var s = &quot;A/B/C/D&quot;;
int from = 1;
var parts = List.of(s.split(&quot;/&quot;));
var res = IntStream.rangeClosed(from, parts.size()).mapToObj(
              i -&gt; i + &quot;/&quot; + String.join(&quot;/&quot;, parts.subList(0, i))).toList();
```

