answers.body_markdown:
See http://ant-contrib.sourceforge.net/tasks/tasks/foreach.html for how to use `foreach`. The `param` must be an **attribute** not a nested element:

    &lt;target name=&quot;copy-all-unzipped&quot;&gt;
        &lt;foreach target=&quot;copy-unzipped&quot; param=&quot;file-path&quot;&gt;
            &lt;fileset dir=&quot;${path.unzipped}&quot;&gt;
                &lt;include name=&quot;**/content.xml&quot;/&gt;
            &lt;/fileset&gt;
        &lt;/foreach&gt;
    &lt;/target&gt;

**EDIT:**

Since the nested fileset element is deprecated, you can replace it with a path element (haven&#39;t tried it, long time since I&#39;ve used Ant...):

    &lt;target name=&quot;copy-all-unzipped&quot;&gt;
        &lt;foreach target=&quot;copy-unzipped&quot; param=&quot;file-path&quot;&gt;
            &lt;path&gt;
                &lt;fileset dir=&quot;${path.unzipped}&quot;&gt;
                   &lt;include name=&quot;**/content.xml&quot;/&gt;
                &lt;/fileset&gt;
            &lt;/path&gt;
        &lt;/foreach&gt;
    &lt;/target&gt;

The example of `&lt;foreach&gt;` you link to is from the [Apache Axis 1.x Ant tasks][1] project. This is a different `&lt;foreach&gt;` than the one from the [Ant-Contrib][2] project.

As manouti says, the Ant-Contrib `&lt;foreach&gt;` doesn&#39;t support nested `param` elements. Instead, the `id` of a `&lt;fileset&gt;` can be passed to the `&lt;target&gt;` and the `&lt;target&gt;` can reference the `id`.

Or, you can use Ant-Contrib&#39;s [`&lt;for&gt;` task][3] (not &quot;`&lt;foreach&gt;`&quot;) which can call a [`&lt;macrodef&gt;`][4]...

    &lt;target name=&quot;copy-all-unzipped&quot;&gt;
        &lt;for param=&quot;file&quot;&gt;
            &lt;path&gt;
                &lt;fileset dir=&quot;${path.unzipped}&quot;&gt;
                    &lt;include name=&quot;**/content.xml&quot;/&gt;
                &lt;/fileset&gt;
            &lt;/path&gt;
            &lt;sequential&gt;
                &lt;copy-unzipped file-path=&quot;@{file}&quot;/&gt;
            &lt;/sequential&gt;
        &lt;/for&gt;
    &lt;/target&gt;
    
    &lt;macrodef name=&quot;copy-unzipped&quot;&gt;
        &lt;attribute name=&quot;file-path&quot;/&gt;
        &lt;sequential&gt;
            &lt;echo&gt;@{file-path}&lt;/echo&gt;
        &lt;/sequential&gt;
    &lt;/macrodef&gt;


  [1]: https://axis.apache.org/axis/java/ant/foreach.html
  [2]: http://ant-contrib.sourceforge.net/tasks/tasks/foreach.html
  [3]: http://ant-contrib.sourceforge.net/tasks/tasks/for.html
  [4]: https://ant.apache.org/manual/Tasks/macrodef.html

